Only when OOW was new, people not knowing pathing or agroing and dying, getting as a result 4 fatties adds in camp due to crappy pathing (as in NW wall camp, just under Hill camp), I have found myself mezzing 2 or 3 mobs here and there, or mezzing adds when a named was pulled and brought along friends due to lack of pulling knowledge or hasty pulls to avoid named ganking. 
<br />

<br />
But after people learnt the zone, I found l myself with pretty much nothing to do (KT flashback) and had to actually request adds on evey pull to keep me entertained. Did I save peeps here and there with mezzes? Sure. Was it really needed? No. I don´t know if you group with gimps or not, but I do know that mezzing more than 1 mob in MPG+ zones every other hour, 5 mobs in WoS every 2 hours, only happens if you artificially  create mez opportunities. 
<br />

<br />
I never felt I was being power leveled cleric-style as I have had with GoD and OOW expansions. Maybe I just was naive all these years, but up untill PoP expansion (included), I always felt as holding my end of the deal.
<br />

<br />
Mezzing once every 2 hours, nuking and slowing just doesn´t cut it for me. 
<br />

<br />
Sometimes, a couple guildies and I are bored and just zone into PoFear just to break it. We get little to no experience and no drops, but gives us something to do and its fun for like 30 minutes.
<br />

<br />
The main problem with EQ in general, and some classes in particular, chanters and monks specially, is the "give us something to do" part. More AAs, spells or levels doesn´t cut it anymore for most. Untill SoE realize this, it is a lost cause.
<br />

<br />
I hear there is a new expansion coming with yet more AAs, and stuff. But hey, we get to kill Dragons now, not Dragorns.Woohoo, FUN!</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
