Seriously. I know two good bards.  Neither of them log in with any regularity.  Do you propose we not build groups when we can't get one?
<br />

<br />
Edit: Seriously.  Everyone who's been on these forums for a few months knows how I feel about bards.  In case you don't, I'll reiterate.  In my opinion, bards are the most F-ing broken class in the game by a huge margin and are currently in need of a serious beatdown with the nerf stick.
<br />

<br />
But that doesn't change the fact that there just aren't a whole lot of them.  I won't attempt to offer an explanation for why, other than that people don't want to be some fruity guy who sings songs, but it's the truth.  
<br />

<br />
Yeah. We stack up real badly next to bards.  But you know, so do a whole asston of classes.   This makes bards broken.  Indeed, one might argue that they're the new 3rd of the Holy Trinaty since they can perform all crowd control tasks (both split pulling and in camp CC) and also provide monstrous other benefits.  (Never underestimate the value of Psalm of Veeshan when every stinking mob you fight has some form of obnoxious, hard to resist proc.)</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
